Privilege Escalation
Root Cause
Authorization decisions were based on a client-controlled HTTP header instead of authenticated user permissions.

Impact
Successful exploitation allows attackers to:

Escalate privileges
Gain administrator access
Execute privileged administrative actions
Completely compromise the application
Prevention
Never use Referer for authorization.
Perform server-side authorization checks on every request.
Validate the authenticated user's role before executing privileged actions.
Treat all client-supplied headers as untrusted input.
